---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ChatInterface from '../components/chat/ChatInterface';
import InfoExtractor from '../components/chat/InfoExtractor';
---

<Layout title="OpenRouter Chat Demo">
  <main class="container mx-auto py-8 px-4">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">OpenRouter API Demo</h1>
    
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Chat Interface</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
          This demo showcases the basic chat functionality using the OpenRouter API.
          You can chat with various AI models like GPT-4o.
        </p>
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow-md">
          <ChatInterface client:load />
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Information Extractor</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
          This demo shows how to use JSON schema to extract structured information from text.
          Try entering a text with personal details to see it extract the data.
        </p>
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow-md">
          <InfoExtractor client:load />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="mt-12 p-6 border rounded-lg bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">About This Demo</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
        This page demonstrates the integration of the OpenRouter service into an Astro application.
        The implementation uses:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li>A TypeScript service class for API communication</li>
        <li>Astro API endpoints for backend processing</li>
        <li>React components for the frontend interface</li>
        <li>JSON schema for structured data extraction</li>
      </ul>
      
      <div class="mt-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Setup Requirements</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">
          To use this demo with your own OpenRouter API key:
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li>Get an API key from <a href="https://openrouter.ai/keys" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">OpenRouter</a></li>
          <li>Add the key to your .env file as <code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded">OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_key_here</code></li>
          <li>Restart the development server</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout> 